cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.DL, cs.GT. 

The paper is about the computational complexity of extending upward planar graph drawings, which is a problem in graph drawing. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algorithms and data structures for solving the problem, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the extensibility of partial representations, which is related to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves proving NP-completeness, which is related to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper discusses a specific version of the problem involving directed paths and cycles, which suggests cs.DL (Digital Libraries) as a possible sub-category.
